Section : 1


Syntax : mkdir [OPTION]... DIRECTORY...


Discription : to allows user to create folders (directly) and you can set permission for folders in same command by option m
and you can create multiple folders in the same command : mkdir file1 file2 ....


Examoles : 1- mkdir -m777 dir1
here , created directly is called dir1 with permission u = rwx , g = rwx , o= rwx


Example 2 : to show message after create directly 
we write this command mkdir -v dir2

after write this command will be print mkdir: created directory 'dir2'
